  "detailedRequirements": "<p>The My Media Share app currently sends a message containing a link to users via SMS; it needs the ability to send links via email as well. &nbsp;This challenge will be tasked with adding the ability to send this message via email.</p>\n\n<p>We have attached the udpated prototype which adds new email address to the current entry page; You should integrate that into the current server code and implement the extra email feature. The submission should also cover mocking scenarios that easily replicate each of the three invokation ways (see below). &nbsp;Overall, once the email is entered the node.js server must handle sending the email to the correct address.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>The email content is simple: &quot;Follow this link to upload a photo to a set top box.&quot; [include the link here]</p>\n\n<p>There are three different ways to enter a phone number on the app, and each of these must work with an email as well.</p>\n\n<p>These are:</p>\n\n<p>1. A URL arrives at the server with the phone number inline as follows: mediasharedev.topcoder.com#1231231234</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Your code must be able to handle mediasharedev.topcoder.com#joe@examples.com</p>\n\n<p>2. Email entry from the main screen, when the app is first loaded.</p>\n\n<p>3. At any time, the user can enter a phone number (or email) and hit okay.</p>\n\n<p>Note:</p>\n\n<p>1. On View Content page, a modal will show up if you start typing in numbers, this needs to be updated to include email field too (see the provided prototype).</p>\n\n<p>2. Please use <a href=\"https://github.com/andris9/Nodemailer\">https://github.com/andris9/Nodemailer</a>&nbsp;for email sending</p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:#FF0000\">Validation</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:#FF0000\">If email address entered is not valid, then the page should execute some basic validation and display a message to the user indicating the email address is not valid..</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:#FF0000\">If there is a failure sending the email, then page should update and display a failure message with high level details.</span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n",
